align=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sharlirafv>SharliraFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/24/03 7:35:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4180.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resists.</span><hr size=1> /ooc<br>
<br>
I don't know the real formula, but I believe the followings are the factors which affect resist checks.<br>
<br>
1.The appropriate resist value of the target of the spell.<br>
2.The resist modifier of the spell. You can check <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Lucy</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> for the exact modifier.<br>
3.The difference of levels between the caster and the target.<br>
<br>
Normally, the difference of levels is more important than resist/modifier. Spells like charms are affected by the charisma of the caster, but I'm not sure if it is also applied to NPC casters.<br>
<br>
Sharlira Silverlight<br>
Circle of Sisters <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=golaghofgrobb>Golagh of Grobb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/24/03 8:01:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4180.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resists.</span><hr size=1> I cannot tell you an exact formula, but Level is definitely the most important factor, specifically, your level in relation to the Mob.  Then Resists are the second factor.<br>
<br>
But it has been my experience that Level is weighted much more.  For example, Lady Vox has an AE Fear.  I found that as a Levl 51, I would resist it every time, while people who were say 47-49 would be affected several times, even if their MR was better than mine by at least 25-50.<br>
<br>
However, individual spells are rated differently, as Lucy can show you, but I wouldn't worry about Resists at low levels - You will find Mobs still sticking spells on you regardless. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thevolcanogod>thevolcanogod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 762<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/24/03 8:32:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4180.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resists.</span><hr size=1> I do remember a while ago they made level a bit less of a factor in whether or not a spell will be resisted both for player - creature and creature - player spells. This meant that even if you were of a much lower level you still had some chance to hit the creature you were casting on. But on the other side, many people were seeing casting creatures landing nukes and DOTs on players twice their level and more.<br>
<br>
They adjusted it too far the first time and brought it back a bit in a later patch. Thats the only resist change I can think of.<br>
<br>
Levels are still #1 way to resist spells and resist gear follows closely behind. <p>Vulrath Vadrigaar<br>
