<br>
I've played a caster that went too long without practicing a certain school of magic (evocation), so her level was much higher than her skill.  When she decided to finally work on it, it was fizzle, fizzle, fizzle, fizzle, cast - full damage.  When she finally does cast, the spell doesn't seem any more resisted than it was at a higher skill level.  The only thing that changed is that she could cast it more reliably.<br>
<br>
As far as I can tell, the casting skill only affects if you fizzle or not.<br>
<br>
I might be wrong, though.  ^_^)) <p>Baroness Titaisia Lightheart<BR>
